ANC mourns the passing of veteran journalist, Ben Said 27 August 2019 The African National Congress conveys its heartfelt condolences to the family of Ben Said, eNCA's Director of News, who passed on yesterday in Mozambique. Ben Said's passing has robbed the media industry of one of its most committed and professional servants. Ben Said was a highly respected journalist who conducted his craft with utmost professionalism and integrity. South Africans who value quality journalism were looking forward to the likes of Ben Said to help groom and empower young journalists who aspire to become the best in this field. His family can take solace in the fact that he leaves behind a proud legacy in the field of journalism. We thank this patriot for his dedication and passion in telling the South African story with honesty and impartiality. The ANC wishes to convey its deepest condolences to his family, friends, colleagues at eNCA and the entire media industry . We wish them strength during this difficult time. May his soul rest in peace. Issued by Pule Mabe, National Spokesperson, ANC, 27 August 2019